00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:49,100
always have to go inside first. You go on the inside, you've

930
00:41:49,100 --> 00:41:51,320
invalidated it because you had the blood of a חטאת *chatas* or

931
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:53,340
the blood of an אשם *asham*. And he says blood of an

932
00:41:53,340 --> 00:41:55,745
אשם *asham* also gets invalidated. But if it's עולה *olah* and שלמים

933
00:41:55,745 --> 00:41:58,200
*shelamim* blood that gets mixed up with inner חטאת *chatas*, bring it

934
00:41:58,200 --> 00:42:01,405
on the inside first, it won't invalidate the עולה *olah* and שלמים

935
00:42:01,405 --> 00:42:04,300
*shelamim*. He doesn't hold like Rabbi Akiva. And then go ahead and

936
00:42:04,300 --> 00:42:07,000
bring it on the outer one. So the גמרא *Gemara* says, yes,

937
00:42:07,100 --> 00:42:09,872
in theory you could do that. אבל כיון דאיכא חטאת ואשם דכי

938
00:42:09,872 --> 00:42:12,580
נכנס דמם פסולים *keivan deika chatas veasham dechi nichnas damam psulim*, since

939
00:42:12,580 --> 00:42:16,045
there are some scenarios where it would invalidate, if it wasn't עולה

940
00:42:16,045 --> 00:42:18,000
*olah* and שלמים *shelamim* blood that got mixed up, but if it

941
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:20,360
was חטאת *chatas* and אשם *asham* blood that got mixed up, that

942
00:42:20,360 --> 00:42:23,274
would invalidate if you brought it on the inside, לא פסיקא ליה

943
00:42:23,274 --> 00:42:25,660
*lo pesika lei*, it's not, it's not categorical.

944
00:42:26,800 --> 00:42:29,380
He's not prepared to say, oh, go ahead, do the inside and

945
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:32,085
then the outside, because that only works by עולה *olah* and שלמים

946
00:42:32,085 --> 00:42:34,429
*shelamim*, it doesn't work by חטאת *chatas* and an אשם *asham*. Okay.

947
